+---
+title: "FIP-Associated Gingivitis in Cats: Why Itraconazole and Lactoferrin Work Better Together"
+date: "2025-11-15"
+slug: "fip-gingivitis-cats-itraconazole-lactoferrin"
+category: "microbiome-research"
+status: "publish"
+excerpt: "Combining an antifungal drug with a natural immune protein solves what single-pathogen thinking cannot—FIP-related gum disease in cats."
+description: "How itraconazole and lactoferrin together target polymicrobial biofilms in FIP-associated gingivitis through drug repurposing, nutritional immunity, and microbial metallomics."
+keywords: "FIP, feline infectious peritonitis, gingivitis, itraconazole, lactoferrin, Candida albicans, Porphyromonas gingivalis, biofilm, nutritional immunity, microbial metallomics, drug repurposing"
+author: "Karen Pendergrass"
+canonicalUrl: "https://karenpendergrass.com/writing/fip-gingivitis-cats-itraconazole-lactoferrin"
+openGraph:
+  title: "FIP-Associated Gingivitis in Cats: Why Itraconazole and Lactoferrin Work Better Together"
+  description: "How itraconazole and lactoferrin together target polymicrobial biofilms in FIP-associated gingivitis through drug repurposing, nutritional immunity, and microbial metallomics."
+  type: "article"
